  "text": "In Envoy v1.31.2, the xDS v2 to v3 API migration is implemented through a dual-version subscription handling architecture that primarily uses versioned proto type conversions and v2-to-v3 field renames at the protocol buffer level.\n\n## Key Findings:\n\n### 1. Proto-Level Migration\nThe proto files in envoyproxy/envoy contain versioning annotations that indicate the v2-to-v3 mapping:\n- `api/envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.proto` contains `option (udpa.annotations.versioning).previous_message_type = \"envoy.api.v2.DiscoveryRequest\"` and similar annotations for DiscoveryResponse and DeltaDiscoveryRequest, showing the v2 predecessors.\n\n### 2. ADS gRPC Server Implementation\n**source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h/cc** implements the legacy Aggregated Discovery Service (ADS) gRPC server:\n- Uses `envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryRequest` and `envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryResponse` exclusively\n- `GrpcMuxImpl` class implements `GrpcMux` interface and `GrpcStreamCallbacks<envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryResponse>`\n- `ApiState` struct maintains per-type-url state with `envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryRequest request_` field\n- The `handleDiscoveryResponse()` method processes v3 responses\n- Dual-version support is achieved through the template-based approach in the newer implementation\n\n### 3. Newer xDS Mux Implementation (Template-Based)\n**source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h/cc** provides the newer, more flexible implementation:\n- Template class `GrpcMuxImpl<S, F, RQ, RS>` where RQ and RS are request/response types\n- `GrpcMuxDelta` specializes with `DeltaDiscoveryRequest` and `DeltaDiscoveryResponse` (both v3)\n- `GrpcMuxSotw` specializes with `DiscoveryRequest` and `DiscoveryResponse` (both v3)\n- This templated architecture allows handling both subscription modes with v3 types\n\n### 4. Subscription State Handlers\n**Delta Subscription State:**\n- `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/delta_subscription_state.h/cc`: Legacy implementation handling `envoy::service::discovery::v3::DeltaDiscoveryResponse`\n- `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.h/cc`: Newer implementation as `BaseSubscriptionState<DeltaDiscoveryResponse, DeltaDiscoveryRequest>`\n- Method `handleResponse(const envoy::service::discovery::v3::DeltaDiscoveryResponse& message)` processes delta responses\n\n**State-of-the-World Subscription State:**\n- `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.h/cc`: Implements SOTW protocol with `envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryRequest` and `DiscoveryResponse`\n- Method `handleGoodResponse(const envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryResponse& message)` processes SOTW responses\n\n### 5. Base Subscription State Template\n**source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/subscription_state.h**:\n- `BaseSubscriptionState<RS, RQ>` template provides common protocol state handling for both delta and SOTW variants\n- `handleResponse(const RS& response)` method handles version management and ACKing\n- All instantiations use v3 proto types (DiscoveryRequest, DiscoveryResponse, DeltaDiscoveryRequest, DeltaDiscoveryResponse)\n\n### 6. gRPC Stream and Failover\n**source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_stream.h** and **grpc_mux_failover.h**:\n- `GrpcStream<RequestProto, ResponseProto>` template handles actual gRPC communication\n- Instantiated with v3 discovery types for both primary and failover streams\n- `sendMessage(const RequestProto& request)` sends v3 requests\n- `onReceiveMessage(ResponseProtoPtr<ResponseProto>&& message)` receives v3 responses\n\n### 7. Version Checking and Validation\n**source/common/config/utility.h/cc**:\n- `Utility::checkTransportVersion()` validates API version configuration\n- Currently rejects v2 transport API version with message: \"The v2 xDS major version has been removed and is no longer supported\"\n- Only allows `ApiVersion::AUTO` or `ApiVersion::V3`\n\n**source/common/config/api_version.h**:\n- Defines `API_NO_BOOST()` macro for forcing specific proto versions (comment mentions preventing API boosting)\n\n### 8. Subscription Factory\n**source/common/config/subscription_factory_impl.h/cc**:\n- `SubscriptionFactoryImpl::subscriptionFromConfigSource()` creates subscriptions\n- Calls `Utility::checkTransportVersion()` to validate v2 is not used\n- Delegates to appropriate subscription type (GRPC, DELTA_GRPC, REST, etc.)\n\n## Migration Strategy\n\nEnvoy v1.31.2 implements v2-to-v3 API migration through:\n\n1. **Protocol Buffer Versioning**: Proto files use UDPA versioning annotations (`udpa.annotations.versioning.previous_message_type`) to document v2-v3 mapping\n\n2. **Field Renames**: The v2-v3 transition involved field name changes (e.g., Node type reference, error handling structure) documented in proto annotations\n\n3. **Template-Based Dual Support**: The xds_mux implementation uses C++ templates to support both SOTW (with DiscoveryRequest/Response) and Delta (with DeltaDiscoveryRequest/Response) xDS modes, all using v3 types\n\n4. **Legacy vs New Implementation**: Two parallel implementations exist:\n   - `grpc_mux_impl`: Direct v3 implementation for backward compatibility\n   - `xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl`: Templated flexible implementation supporting both subscription modes\n\n5. **Version Enforcement**: The configuration layer explicitly rejects v2 transport API versions, forcing migration to v3\n\n## Important Note\n\nIn Envoy v1.31.2, **v2 support has been completely removed from the source code**. The v2 proto definitions still exist in the repository (api/envoy/api/v2/ and api/envoy/service/discovery/v2/) for reference and documentation purposes, but the C++ implementation uses only v3 types. The dual-version subscription handling is achieved through:\n- Template specialization for Delta vs SOTW modes (both v3)\n- Proto versioning annotations indicating v2-v3 mapping\n- Configuration validation preventing v2 usage\n\nThe actual v2-to-v3 conversion would have occurred at proto-generation time during the API migration phase, not at runtime in this version of Envoy."
